name: 10" 80TPI Blade for Aluminum, 5/8" Arbor
Group_Name: Metal Devil® Metal Cutting Circular Saw Blades
meta_description: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teet
short_description:
Features & Benefits

  • Very little friction created while cutting due to the unique metallurgy of the blades, transfering heat away from the work-piece so it can be immediately handled
  • Hardly any vibration. Feels like cutting through wood rather than steel
  • Blades range from 5-3/8" to 14" (137-356mm) in diameter
  • Blades reach their full potential when used on special metal cutting circular saws
  • Designed to cut angle iron, c-channel, steel plate, thin steel, trusses, rebar, joists, conduit, grading, and aluminum
  • Tungsten carbide tipped blade for longer blade life
summary: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teeth on the blade, carbide grade and the shape of the teeth. (1) per card

Group_Name: Metal Devil® Metal Cutting Circular Saw Blades
meta_description: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teet
description: 12" 60TPI Blade for Steel, 1" Arbor
short_description:
Features & Benefits

  • Very little friction created while cutting due to the unique metallurgy of the blades, transfering heat away from the work-piece so it can be immediately handled
  • Hardly any vibration. Feels like cutting through wood rather than steel
  • Blades range from 5-3/8" to 14" (137-356mm) in diameter
  • Blades reach their full potential when used on special metal cutting circular saws
  • Designed to cut angle iron, c-channel, steel plate, thin steel, trusses, rebar, joists, conduit, grading, and aluminum
  • Tungsten carbide tipped blade for longer blade life
summary: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teeth on the blade, carbide grade and the shape of the teeth. (1) per card

name: 1-7/8" Hole Saw
meta_description: This premium line of professional quality hole saws features an M3 high-speed steel cutting edge, electron beam welded to a tough steel backer. Caps stand up to abuse and punishment, yet are lighter and easier to use than those of competitors. Positive ra
short_description:
This premium line of professional quality hole saws features an M3 high-speed steel cutting edge, electron beam welded to a tough steel backer. Caps stand up to abuse and punishment, yet are lighter and easier to use than those of competitors. Positive rake tooth design provides better chip clearance as teeth cut into wood, plastic or any machinable metal.

  • Backer, cutting edge and cap work together to provide faster, longer-lasting cutting action
  • Bi-metal design bonds M3 cutting edge to fatigue resistant backer
  • Positive rake teeth clear chips better for longer life and easier cutting
  • Teeth stay sharper and make smoother cuts

small_image_label: Metal Devil® Metal Cutting Circular Saw Blades 9"
thumbnail_label: Metal Devil® Metal Cutting Circular Saw Blades 9"
short_description:
Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teeth on the blade, carbide grade and the shape of the teeth. (1) per card

  • Very little friction created while cutting due to the unique metallurgy of the blades, transfering heat away from the work-piece so it can be immediately handled
  • Hardly any vibration. Feels like cutting through wood rather than steel
  • Blades range from 5-3/8" to 14" (137-356mm) in diameter
  • Blades reach their full potential when used on special metal cutting circular saws
  • Designed to cut angle iron, c-channel, steel plate, thin steel, trusses, rebar, joists, conduit, grading, and aluminum
  • Tungsten carbide tipped blade for longer blade life
summary:
Applications:
  • Metal cutting

name: HOLESAW 11/16" #170116
description:
Premium line of professional quality bi-metal hole saws feature an M3 high-speed steel cutting edge, electron beam welded
to a tough steel backer. Caps stand up to abuse and punishment, yet are lighter and easier to use than those of competitors.
Cutting
short_description:
Positive rake teeth provides better chip clearance
  • 1 1/2" cutting depth will cut through a 2 x 4
  • Requires a separate arbor.
  • Variable pitch teeth reduces friction and heat
  • Expanded gullets allow for faster cutting and increased blade life
  • Better tooth match for better chip clearance and smoother cutting
  • Reinforced tooth flank makes teeth stronger for longer life and
  • resistance to tooth strippage.
